* Unit Vector
:PROPERTIES:
:ID:       a205bbaf-4e49-4e20-baab-3c4ad49fac41
:END:
** Formula
\begin{align*}
U = \frac{v}{\lVert v \rVert}
\end{align*}
** Example
Given that we have: $V = \langle 4, -3 \rangle$:
Find the unit vector of it:
\begin{align*}
& U = \frac{V}{\lVert v \rVert}
= \frac{\langle4, -3\rangle}{5}
= \left\langle \frac{4}{5}, \frac{-3}{5} \right\rangle \\
& \lVert v \rVert
= \sqrt{4^2 + (-3)^2}
= \sqrt{16 + 9}
= \sqrt{25}
= 5
\end{align*}
